KAIZER Chiefs have confirmed the passing of the clubs Under-19 development player in a fatal car accident. Amakhosi Under-19 midfielder James McFarlane succumbed to serious injuries following a horrific accident in Johannesburg on Friday. The former Amajimbos young prospect had captain was once Chiefs under-17 captain and he was a regular feature in Molefi Ntseki's junior national team. Chiefs confirmed his passing in a statement released on Twitter on Friday afternoon. "Gone too soon," the club said. "It is with great sadness that we announce the passing due to a car accident of our U19 Youth Development Academy player, James Mcfarlene. We pass our heartfelt condolences to the bereaved family and friends. May his soul Rest In Eternal Peace." Gone too soon.It is with great sadness that we announce the passing due to a car accident of our U19 Youth Development Academy player, James Mcfarlene. We pass our heartfelt condolences to the bereaved family and friends. May his soul Rest In Eternal Peace.#Amakhosi4Life pic.twitter.com/E6hZxtWjuk   